in a critical perspective on how plantation life is changing as Darjeeling struggles to reinvent its signature commodity for twenty-first-century consumers. The Darjeeling Distinction challenges fair-trade policy and practice, exposing how trade initiatives often fail to consider the larger environmental, historical, and sociopolitical forces that shape the lives of the people they intended to support.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCompetition, UnfairzIndiazDarjeeling (District). 0aTea plantationszIndiaxDarjeeling (District). 0aTea plantationszIndiazDarjeeling (District). 0aTea tradezIndiazDarjeeling (District). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  acolonial rule.  adarjeeling.  adisciplines.  aenvironmental studies.  aexpensive tea.  afair trade practices.  afairness.  ageography.  ahimalayan foothills.  ajustice.  anortheast india.  anuanced ethnography.  apostcolonial separatist politics.  aregion.  aregional autonomy.  asociology.  atea industry.  atea leaves.  atea workers.  avalue.  aviolent movement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027739740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095760240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957602423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957602/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY